Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper focuses on extracting semantic information from audio segments. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a deep neural network architecture for unsupervised learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the development of a model for learning vector representations of audio segments. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely as the paper does not deal with image or video data.
